caption.text:
Exactly one year I live in this crowded city. I hadn't expect to live here till I got a work placement and force myself to hold on everytime I wanna give up. Yap, cause my heart stays in Bandung. I still remember how sad I was every week when I had to go back to Jakarta for the first-six-months. Honestly not only sad, I cried. I cried for leaving my home, my family, my friends and my love. I thanked God I could still go home every weekend but still Monday to Friday had to go through. 
But now, I thank God once again, I'm still here with a big hearted, starting to enjoy my days here, got so many nice friends and never cry again unless I got sick and miss my home badly. And the most important thing is that I never learn before, now I always appreciate my golden time, my quality time with all people I love. Cause it's the best treasure that I got in every weekend :)
At the beginning, it's hard, I don't think that I can hold on for long. But in the end, I know His plans never fail. You can't ask to live in your comfort zone and learn to grow. You have to get out and challenge yourself. Cause in the end, every place could be your comfort zone. It depends on you! :)
